
Overview of verb notice

The verb notice has 4 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (39) detect, observe, find, discover, notice -- (discover or determine the existence, presence, or fact of; "She detected high levels of lead in her drinking water"; "We found traces of lead in the paint")
2. (19) notice, mark, note -- (notice or perceive; "She noted that someone was following her"; "mark my words")
3. (1) comment, notice, remark, point out -- (make or write a comment on; "he commented the paper of his colleague")
4. notice, acknowledge -- (express recognition of the presence or existence of, or acquaintance with; "He never acknowledges his colleagues when they run into him in the hallway"; "She acknowledged his complement with a smile"; "it is important to acknowledge the work of others in one's own writing")
